Description: Optionally skip auth-required repos when HTTP_AUTH is unset.
 When a repository returns HTTP 401 (EACCES) and no HTTP_AUTH is provided,
 apk normally aborts. This makes that non-fatal for an allowlist of
 repositories: the repository is dropped with a warning and apk continues.
 Auth failures with HTTP_AUTH set, or for repositories not on the allowlist,
 remain fatal.
 .
 The allowlist is a comma/space separated list of fnmatch(3) glob patterns,
 matched case-insensitively against the "host/path" of each repository URL.
 It is resolved from, in order: the --allow-missing-auth command line option,
 the APK_ALLOW_MISSING_AUTH environment variable, and the
 APK_DEFAULT_ALLOW_MISSING_AUTH compile-time default (unset upstream).
Author: Łukasz Zemczak <lukasz.zemczak@chainguard.dev>
Forwarded: https://gitlab.alpinelinux.org/alpine/apk-tools/-/merge_requests/410

